  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Leasing Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist management to formulate and implement strategic sales and marketing plans to maximise the sales volume and leasing activities for 3 of our companies industrial properties at Senoko Road and Burn Road.</li>\n  <li>Assist management to establish and maintain relationship with key decision makers in the leasing network, including small, middle and/or large corporates</li>\n  <li>Identify and negotiate with potential tenants on new leases and follow through with all documentation (including tenancy agreement) to complete the lease transaction</li>\n  <li>Maintain good relationship with existing tenants and handle all lease renewals</li>\n  <li>Execute marketing and communication activities for (a) tenant relationship management and (b) to build up network of potential tenants</li>\n  <li>Meet or exceed the targets set for the portfolio of properties responsible for</li>\n  <li>Will be involved in budgeting or costing activities</li>\n  <li>Any other duties assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Tertiary education in Real Estate/Building Management/Marketing or any related discipline</li>\n  <li>At least 1 year of relevant experience</li>\n  <li>Strong presentation and negotiation skills.</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge of the tenancy agreement process and documentation for leasing</li>\n  <li>Should have some facility maintenance or engineering knowledge to manage the assigned properties effectively</li>\n  <li>Good track record in office sales and leasing</li>\n  <li>Well organized, meticulous and highly numerate</li>\n  <li>Strong oral and written communication skills, as well as interpersonal and tenant relationship management skills</li>\n  <li>Resourceful, self-motivated and able to work independently as well as part of a team in a constantly evolving environment</li>\n</ul>",
